name: Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Sit on the floor, legs extended. Reach forward and try to touch your toes.

name: Quad Stretch
instructions: Stand on one leg and pull the opposite foot toward your glutes, holding your ankle with your hand.

name: Chest Stretch
instructions: Extend your arms behind you and clasp your hands together. Gently raise your arms to open up the chest.

name: Triceps Stretch
instructions: Raise one arm overhead and bend your elbow so that your hand touches your upper back. Use the opposite hand to gently press the elbow for a deeper stretch.

name: Cat-Cow Stretch
instructions: On all fours, inhale and arch your back (cow), then exhale and round your back (cat), moving between both positions.

name: Seated Forward Fold
instructions: Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front. Slowly fold forward, reaching for your feet or ankles.

name: Cobra Stretch
instructions: Lie face down, place your hands under your shoulders, and press into the floor as you lift your chest upward.

name: Hip Flexor Stretch
instructions: Lunge forward with one leg, keeping your back knee on the ground and pressing your hips forward to stretch the hip flexors.

name: Side Stretch
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart. Raise one arm overhead and lean to the opposite side, stretching the side of your body.

name: Neck Stretch
instructions: Gently tilt your head toward one shoulder, feeling a stretch on the side of your neck. Hold and switch sides.

name: Butterfly Stretch
instructions: Sit with your feet together and knees out to the sides. Gently press your knees toward the floor to stretch your inner thighs.

name: Standing Forward Fold
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart. Slowly bend forward at the hips, letting your head and neck relax toward the floor.

name: Childâ€™s Pose
instructions: Kneel on the floor, then sit back on your heels and stretch your arms forward on the floor, lowering your chest toward the ground.

name: Russian Twist
instructions: Lie on your back with arms outstretched. Bring one knee to your chest and then let it drop to the opposite side, keeping your shoulders on the floor.

name: Lower Back Stretch
instructions: Lie on your back with knees bent. Gently pull your knees toward your chest and hold for a deeper stretch in your lower back.

name: Wrist Stretch
instructions: Extend one arm forward with the palm up. With the opposite hand, gently pull the fingers back toward your body to stretch the wrist and forearm.

name: Calf Stretch
instructions: Stand with one foot behind the other and press your back heel into the floor to stretch your calf.

name: Standing Hip Stretch
instructions: Stand tall and place one ankle on the opposite knee. Gently press down on the raised knee to stretch the hip.

name: Pigeon Pose
instructions: From a kneeling position, extend one leg behind you while bringing the other leg forward and bending it at the knee. Lower your torso toward the floor to stretch the hip.

name: Wall Chest Stretch
instructions: Stand near a wall, place your hand on the wall, and gently rotate your torso away from the wall to stretch the chest and shoulders.

name: Resistance Band Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Lie on your back and loop a resistance band around the ball of one foot. Gently pull the band toward you to stretch the hamstring.

name: Foam Roller Calf Stretch
instructions: Place the foam roller under your calves. Lift your hips and roll back and forth to massage the calf muscles and stretch them.

name: Band-Assisted Shoulder Stretch
instructions: Hold a resistance band with both hands. Pull the band overhead, stretching the shoulders and upper back.

name: Kettlebell Shoulder Stretch
instructions: Hold a kettlebell with both hands and raise it overhead. Use your opposite hand to gently stretch the triceps and shoulders.

name: Foam Roller Upper Back Stretch
instructions: Place the foam roller under your upper back. Cross your arms over your chest, and gently roll back and forth to stretch the upper back.

name: Dumbbell Chest Stretch
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and extend your arms out to the sides, gently pulling them back to stretch the chest.

name: Barbell Hip Flexor Stretch
instructions: Place a barbell on your hips while lying on your back. Slowly raise your hips towards the ceiling to stretch the hip flexors.

name: Stretching with a Resistance Band
instructions: Hold a resistance band in both hands, extend it overhead, and stretch to the side to engage the shoulders and upper body.

name: Seated Band Hip Stretch
instructions: Sit on the floor, place a resistance band around your foot, and pull it toward your chest to stretch the hip.

name: Foam Roller IT Band Stretch
instructions: Lie on your side with the foam roller under your outer thigh. Roll gently to stretch the IT band.

name: Kettlebell Triceps Stretch
instructions: Hold a kettlebell in one hand overhead, and with the opposite hand, gently press your elbow to deepen the triceps stretch.

name: Foam Roller Lower Back Stretch
instructions: Lie on your back and place the foam roller under your lower back. Gently rock side to side to release tension in the lower back.

name: Resistance Band Shoulder Stretch
instructions: Hold a resistance band with both hands and stretch it across your chest to stretch your shoulders.

name: Dumbbell Side Stretch
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in one hand and lean to the opposite side, stretching your obliques.

name: Foam Roller Adductor Stretch
instructions: Place the foam roller under your inner thigh and gently roll back and forth to release tension in your adductors.

name: Resistance Band Quadriceps Stretch
instructions: Stand tall and wrap a resistance band around your ankle, gently pulling it towards your glutes to stretch the quadriceps.

name: Medicine Ball Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Place one leg on a medicine ball, extend your leg, and lean forward to stretch the hamstring.

name: Dumbbell Chest Opener
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and open your chest by extending your arms wide to stretch the chest muscles.

name: Barbell Overhead Stretch
instructions: Hold a barbell with both hands overhead. Gently lean to each side to stretch the shoulders and upper body.

name: Kettlebell Lunge Stretch
instructions: Hold a kettlebell in one hand and perform a lunge with your opposite leg forward. Use the kettlebell to deepen the hip flexor stretch.

name: Foam Roller T-Spine Stretch
instructions: Place the foam roller under your upper back. Place your hands behind your head and gently roll to stretch the thoracic spine.

name: Resistance Band Glute Stretch
instructions: Place a resistance band around your knees and sit down with your feet flat. Gently open your knees to stretch the glutes.

name: Dumbbell Side Lateral Stretch
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in one hand and raise it sideways to stretch the side of your torso and arms.

name: Barbell Chest Stretch
instructions: Place a barbell on a rack or hold it in front of your chest. Gently extend your arms outward to stretch the chest muscles.

name: Stretching with Foam Roller
instructions: Roll the foam roller along your back, legs, or arms to stretch and release muscle tension.
